project SubcommandDispatcher

task ParseArgvWithSubcommand
    goal
        Parse an argv list into a subcommand plus flags, options, and remaining positional args.
    input
        argv
    output
        parsed
    constraint
        Function name is parse_subcommand.
        Module is impl.py.
        Return value is a dict with keys subcommand, flags, options, positional.
        subcommand is str or None. flags is a set. options is a dict. positional is a list.
        The first bare (non-dash) token before -- becomes the subcommand.
    test
        Empty argv returns subcommand None with empty rest.
        A single bare token becomes the subcommand.
        Bare token then another bare goes to subcommand and positional.
        Flags before the subcommand are captured.
        Flags after the subcommand are captured.
        A dash-dash-key-equals-value option is captured.
        A dash-dash by itself ends option parsing and yields no subcommand from later tokens.
        A positional after a discovered subcommand is preserved.
        Non-list argv raises TypeError.
    success
        Every acceptance case above matches exactly.
